  ---
  Without a marketplace config, installation comes down to two options:

  Option 1: Manual copy/clone (always works)

  # Clone the repo
  git clone https://github.com/matrixport/skills.git

  # Copy the skill to your personal Claude Code skills directory
  cp -r skills/matrixport/skills/skills/matrixport/us-equity ~/.claude/skills/us-equity

  That's it. Claude Code automatically scans ~/.claude/skills/ (global) and .claude/skills/
  (project-level). The skill becomes available immediately.

  Option 2: npx skills add (agentskills CLI by Vercel)

  npx skills add matrixport/skills --skill skills/matrixport/us-equity

  Under the hood it:
  1. Clones the GitHub repo to a temp location
  2. Finds the skill directory you specified
  3. Copies it to .claude/skills/us-equity/ (project) or ~/.claude/skills/us-equity/ (global
  with -g)

  It's just automating the manual copy — no registry, no server, just git clone + file copy.

  ---
  So in plain terms

  The plugin marketplace system exists purely to give users a nicer one-liner (/plugin
  install). Without it, the underlying mechanism is simply "copy the skill directory to the
  right place."

  Your repo structure is already correct. The install story for users is just:
  npx skills add matrixport/skills --skill skills/matrixport/us-equity
  or a manual clone. No marketplace config needed unless you want the Claude Code /plugin
  install UX.

  ---
  Claude Code plugin marketplace

  /plugin marketplace add matrixport/skills
  /plugin install us-equity@matrixport-skills
  A marketplace is just a GitHub repo with a marketplace.json catalog file. That catalog
  lists plugins (each plugin can contain one or more skills). Claude Code fetches the
  catalog, then fetches and installs the referenced plugin. No registry, no server — just
  GitHub.
